SUMMARY:A Storytelling Workshop: What's Your Story?
DESCRIPTION:Do you want to turn a real moment from your life into a story that connects? 🎤✨ \nReplay Storytelling is excite to present this seven-week\, hands-on storytelling workshop will help you take moments from your life and turn them into vibrant\, compelling stories that connect with an audience. \nSpace is limited–register now: https://replaystorytelling.com/events/whats-your-story/ \nWhether you’re brand new to storytelling or looking to hone your skills\, we’ll help you shape\, structure\, and find the heart of your stories — bringing them fully to life. \nAlong the way\, you’ll discover how storytelling can strengthen your communication skills\, deepen connection\, and help you share your experiences with confidence and clarity. \nIn this workshop\, you’ll learn how to:• Tell your story with clarity\, empathy\, and vulnerability.• Find the emotional heart and truth of your experiences.• Shape your story through structure\, pace and using vivid detail.• Work with suspense\, humour and emotion.• Develop characters\, find your voice\, and point of view.• Identify the moments that matter most—and let go of the rest.• Apply practical techniques to confidently perform and share your story. \nBy the end of the workshop\, you’ll leave with a story that’s honest\, engaging\, and ready to be shared on stage — including the opportunity to perform at Replay Story Fest 3 this April! \n🗓️ Tuesday\, March 3rd — Tuesday\, April 14th\, 2026🕥 6:30pm — 9:30pm (Each Week)📍 Balzac’s Powerhouse | 29 Powerhouse Street \nCost: $300 \n* Please note: the student showcase will take place at the Burdock Music Hall | 1184 Bloor Street West \n#themoth #thingstodointoronto #storytellingto #storytellingtoronto #torontoworkshops #storytellingworkshops #truestoriestoldlive #workshops #learn #howtotellyourstory #Toronto_events #LiveStorytelling #TorontoArts #PersonalStorytelling
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/a-storytelling-workshop-whats-your-story/
LOCATION:Balzac’s Coffee (29 Powerhouse Street\, Toronto)\, 29 Powerhouse Street\, Toronto\, Toronto\, M6H 0C7
CATEGORIES:Classes & Workshops,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/a-storytelling-workshop-whats-your-story.jpg
END:VEVENT
