SUMMARY:Comedy Game Showdown: Hogtown Follies!
DESCRIPTION:Featured at FanExpo\, Toronto ComiCon\, and the Montreal Fringe Festival\, Comedy Game Showdown is Toronto’s longest-running comedy panel show! \nEach episode\, two teams of Toronto’s finest comedians face off in a series of quizzes\, games\, and debates to see who will win the game\, and with it…the people’s ovation and fame forever! \nTheme for March 3: Hogtown Follies \nFrom the Battle of York to the City of Pork and Hollywood North to  the tasty Danforth\, anything and everything to do with our fair city might come up as our two teams of contestants face off to see who gets  to Ride the Rocket and who gets nixxed in the 6ix! \nThe Yonge Turks: Nikki Ashworth\, Simon Rakoff\, Gerald Yeung \nThe Bay Street Rollers: Charlotte Davie\, Andrew Lizotte\, Marc Hallworth \nHosted by Dan Donnelly \nMarch 3 – 7:30pm – John Candy Box Theatre1 York Street\, TorontoTickets $25
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/comedy-game-showdown-hogtown-follies/
LOCATION:John Candy Box Theatre\, 1 York St\, Toronto\, ON M5J 0B6\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M5J 0B6
CATEGORIES:Comedy & Improv,Games & Trivia,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/comedy-game-showdown-hogtown-follies.png
END:VEVENT
