SUMMARY:I Carry with Me
DESCRIPTION:Mixed Company Theatre presents “I Carry with Me”\, a Forum Theatre production written\, directed\, and facilitated by Heather Cherron von Atzigen. \nPlay Description:A trip to a coffee shop quickly turns Faiza’s day into one of fear\, humiliation and abandonment. No doubt her race\, faith and traditional dress played a factor. Nurse Mailynn has trouble finding support from her supervisor and co-workers after a patient refuses to be treated by her because of her race. Masego feels dismissed after sharing a frightening incident both she and her son experienced. How are things going to change for people who are racialized when her own partner and the police keep making excuses? \n“I Carry with Me” is a play that looks at the differences and commonalities in what we carry as human beings from different racial and cultural backgrounds. What we carry can hurt\, show similarities\, educate\, be shared\, and enlighten. \nJoin us at this interactive performance to stand up\, make changes in these stories\, and discover actions you can take to foster inclusive and supportive spaces for people of all cultural backgrounds. \nContent Note: This presentation depicts situations of racial tension and harassment. \nThis production is funded by the Government of Canada’s Department of Canadian Heritage\, the Toronto Arts Council\, the Catherine and Maxwell Meighen Foundation\, and the Ontario Arts Council. \nPerformance Schedule & Locations: \n\nTuesday March 3\, 7:30 pm (ET) at East End United Regional Ministry\, Eastminster Campus\, 310 Danforth Avenue\, Toronto\nWednesday March 4\, 7:30 pm (ET) at The Experience Centre\, 240 The East Mall\, Etobicoke\nThursday March 5\, 7:30 pm (ET) at the Performing Arts Lodges\, 110 The Esplanade\, Toronto\nSaturday March 7\, 2:00 pm (ET) at Grant African Methodist Episcopal Church\, 2029 Gerrard St E\, Toronto\n\nRegistration:For most performances you can register to reserve your seat in advance. “Pay What You Can” donations are welcome. Please see our website for full information. \nFull Performance Details: https://mixedcompanytheatre.com/i-carry-with-me/
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/i-carry-with-me/
LOCATION:East End United\, 310 Danforth Ave\, Toronto\, ON M4K 1N6\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M4K 1N6
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Performing Arts,Theatre & Opera
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/i-carry-with-me.png
END:VEVENT
